The '''Unit for the History and Philosophy of Science''' (HPS) is a constituent body of the [[Sydney Faculty of Science|Faculty of Science]] at the [[University of Sydney]], [[Australia]]. The HPS offers undergraduate and post-graduate programs in the history, philosophy and social studies of science and medicine and, jointly with the [[Centre for Values, Ethics and the Law in Medicine]] (VELiM), administers the [[Sydney Bioethics Program]] .
==History== The first lecture series in History and Philosophy of Science was offered to science students in 1945. Classes started in 1953. <ref name="about_hps">http://sydney.edu.au/science/hps/about/profile.shtml</ref>
